{
  "Oceans (Currents, Salinity, Temperature Layers)": "海洋(当前、盐度、温度层)",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is the thermohaline circulation?": "什么是热水循环?",
  "The thermohaline circulation (also called the global ocean conveyor belt) is a worldwide system of deep currents driven by differences in water density from temperature (thermo) and salinity (haline) variations, taking approximately 1,000 years for water to complete the full circuit.": "热水环流(又称全球海洋传送带)是一个由温度(热量)和盐度(盐度)变化水密度差异所驱动的世界性深流系统,水大约需要1 000年才能完成整个电路。",
  "What is upwelling?": "什么是上房?",
  "Upwelling occurs when persistent winds blow surface water away from a coast or the equator, and cold, nutrient-rich deep water rises to replace it, creating highly productive zones that support abundant marine life and major fisheries.": "当长风将表层水吹离海岸或赤道,而冷、富营养的深水上升取而代之,形成高产区,支持丰富的海洋生物和主要渔业时,就会出现上升。",
  "What is a halocline?": "什么是卤化物?",
  "A halocline is a vertical zone in the ocean where salinity changes rapidly with depth, often found where fresher surface water (from rainfall or river input) sits above saltier deep water, creating a density barrier between the two layers.": "卤化物是海洋的一个垂直区,盐度随深度而迅速变化,常常发现较新鲜的地表水(来自降雨或河流输入)位于咸度深水之上,造成两层之间的密度屏障。",
  "What is ocean stratification?": "什么是海洋分层?",
  "Ocean stratification refers to the natural layering of ocean water into horizontal zones of different density, with warm, less dense water on top and cold, dense water below, separated by the thermocline, and this stratification affects mixing, nutrient distribution, and marine life.": "海洋分层是指海洋水的自然层层分入不同密度的横向区域,顶部有温暖的、较不稠密的水,下面有冷的、密密水,由温度线分离,这种分层影响混合、养分分布和海洋生物。",
  "What is the Ekman spiral?": "什么是艾克曼螺旋?",
  "The Ekman spiral describes how wind-driven water movement changes direction with depth: the surface layer moves at an angle to the wind due to the Coriolis effect, and each successive deeper layer moves at a greater angle with diminishing speed, creating a spiral pattern.": "Ekman螺旋说明风驱动的水运动如何以深度改变方向:由于Coriolis效应,地表层向风角移动,每一层相继的更深层向更大的角移动,速度下降,形成螺旋模式。",
  "What is a pycnocline?": "什么是侏儒症?",
  "A pycnocline is a zone where water density changes rapidly with depth, typically coinciding with the thermocline and halocline, and it acts as a significant barrier to vertical mixing, separating the well-mixed surface layer from the deep ocean.": "俾科诺明线是水密度随深度而迅速变化的区域,通常与热线和卤化物同时发生,并成为垂直混合的重大障碍,将混合好的表层与深海分开。",
  "What is ocean acidification?": "什么是海洋酸化?",
  "Ocean acidification occurs as the ocean absorbs about 25-30% of atmospheric CO2, which reacts with seawater to form carbonic acid, lowering pH and threatening shell-forming organisms like corals, shellfish, and certain plankton species.": "海洋酸化发生时,海洋吸收了约25%-30%的大气二氧化碳,与海水发生反应,形成碳酸,降低pH值,并威胁形成珊瑚、贝类和某些浮游生物等贝壳的生物。",
  "What is an ocean gyre?": "什么是海洋旋翼?",
  "An ocean gyre is a large system of circular surface currents driven by global wind patterns and deflected by the Coriolis effect and continental boundaries, with five major subtropical gyres (North and South Atlantic, North and South Pacific, and Indian Ocean) dominating ocean circulation.": "海洋环流是一个大型环状海面流系统,由全球风势驱动,受科里奥利斯效应和大陆边界的偏移,五大亚热带环流(北大西洋和南大西洋、北太平洋和南太平洋以及印度洋)主导海洋环流。",
  "What is the mixed layer of the ocean?": "什么是海洋的混合层?",
  "The mixed layer is the upper portion of the ocean (typically 20 to 200 meters deep) where wind, waves, and surface heating create a relatively uniform temperature throughout, sitting above the thermocline where temperature drops rapidly.": "混合层是海洋的上层(一般为20至200米深),风、波浪和表面加热在整个温度上方形成相对统一的温度,温度迅速下降。",
  "What is Ekman transport?": "什么是埃克曼运输?",
  "Ekman transport is the net movement of the wind-driven water column at roughly 90 degrees to the right of the wind direction in the Northern Hemisphere (left in the Southern), and this process is responsible for coastal upwelling and the convergence of water in subtropical gyres.": "Ekman运输是风力水柱的净移动,大约在90度,向北半球风向右移动(左在南方),这一过程造成沿海上涌和亚热带旋流中水的汇合。",
  "Average ocean salinity is approximately:": "平均海洋盐度约为:",
  "Average ocean salinity is approximately 35 parts per thousand (or 3.5%), meaning each kilogram of seawater contains about 35 grams of dissolved salts, primarily sodium chloride.": "平均海洋盐度约为每千分之35(3.5%),即每公斤海水含约35克溶解盐,主要是氯化钠。"
}